{
  "_doc": "Shared gate for run_eval.py and the report. A change is a regression when it moves the worse way by more than max(abs_floor, baseline*rel_tol). hard_min/hard_max are absolute non-tradeable bounds; trigger/trigger_min create baseline-independent issues. required_evidence marks primary metrics that every applicable clip must produce; optional primary metrics are compared when present on both sides, while one-sided absence is always inconclusive.",
  "_pop_note": "exact_pop_spread_pct is p95-p5 of the exact signed full-binocular disparity produced by the shipping HLSL and is the primary stereo-volume gate. It is normalized to reference-aspect-equivalent image disparity at the 5120x2160 stream aspect. Image phase-correlation pop metrics remain diagnostic because repetitive textures can produce false disparity aliases. The +/-3% comfort tails use the same exact HLSL field but are not a fixed angular guarantee because the XR panel can be moved and resized: disparity angle is approximately 3% of the panel's apparent horizontal angle (about 1 degree at a 33-degree-wide panel, or 1.8 degrees at 60 degrees). Revisit the threshold if the product fixes presentation FOV or user comfort testing establishes a different bound.",
  "metrics": {
    "exact_pop_spread_pct": {"role": "primary", "axis": "stereo", "better": "higher", "rel_tol": 0.15, "abs_floor": 0.04, "evidence": "exact_hlsl_full_binocular_disparity", "required_evidence": true},
    "pop_spread_pct": {"role": "diagnostic", "axis": "stereo", "better": "higher", "rel_tol": 0.15, "abs_floor": 0.04},
    "pop_spread_px": {"role": "diagnostic", "axis": "stereo", "better": "higher", "rel_tol": 0.15, "abs_floor": 1.0},
